In [ ]:
# Expand color range for each group by 5% in each direction. To account for
# slight variations in color
color_ranges = {
    "First": ([235, 242, 243], [255, 255, 255]),
    "Second": ([190, 237, 214], [198, 245, 222]),
    "Three": ([176, 215, 237], [184, 223, 245]),
    "Four": ([232, 239, 242], [240, 247, 250])
}

# Mask for each group
masks = {}
for group, (lower, upper) in color_ranges.items():
    lower = np.array(lower, dtype=np.uint8)
    upper = np.array(upper, dtype=np.uint8)
    mask = cv2.inRange(geo_scan, lower, upper)
    masks[group] = mask

# Plot each mask
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
for i, (group, mask) in enumerate(masks.items()):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i+1)
    plt.imshow(mask, cmap="gray")
    plt.title(group)
    plt.grid(False)
plt.show()
